text: Maytenus harenensis is a species of plant in the family Celastraceae. It is endemic to the Harenna Forest in southeastern Ethiopia, a remnant Afromontane forest in the Bale Mountains. It is threatened by habitat loss. ==References== harenensis Category:Endemic flora of Ethiopia Category:Trees of Ethiopia Category:Bale Mountains Category:Ethiopian Highlands Category:Afromontane flora Category:Vulnerable flora of Africa Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
